  1. JVM(Java Virtual Machine) acts as a run-time engine to run Java applications.
  2. It provides a runtime environment for Java applications to run on different platforms and operating systems.
  3. one of the main advantages of JVM is its platform independence.
  4. JVM supports dynamic class loading and unloading. It provides application programming interfaces (APIs) such as ClassLoader that allow classes to be loaded dynamically at runtime. 
 What it does?
   The JVM performs following operation:
     Loads code 
     Verifies code
     Executes code
     Provides runtime environment